Sanction letter for EMI Loan Restructuring






Date: <%= data.currentDate %>






                Dear
                    <%= data.customerName %>,





            Thank you for opting for the restructuring of your loan. Please find below the revised terms and
                conditions applicable to your restructured loan account. Kindly read them carefully and retain a copy
                for your records.
                <a href=<%=data.lender.lender_info.base_url %>><%= data.lender.lender_info.base_url %>





                We are pleased to sanction you a loan as per the enclosed terms and
                Schedule of Loan Sanction Terms:





                Please note that this sanction letter is issued in response to your loan application and based on the
                information you have provided to us.





                The Restructuring fees as charged is mentioned in the schedule and the same will be deducted from your
                loan amount upfront.




            You are under no obligation to accept the sanctioned loan. If you do not accept the sanction letter and
                the enclosed agreement your loan application will be considered withdrawn and you will not be liable to
                pay any restructuring fees/charges.





                The loan will be disbursed to your below-mentioned bank account after confirmation and acceptance of
                this sanction letter.




            1. Acknowledgment of Dues:



            You acknowledge and confirm the outstanding principal, interest, and applicable charges as of the date
                of restructuring. This total will form the principal of your restructured loan.




            2. Restructured Loan Amount:






The revised loan amount includes:

Outstanding principal : <%= data.newPrincipalLoanAmount %>


Accrued but unpaid interest : <%= data.totalInterestAmount %>


Applicable charges/fees, if capitalized: <% data.totalRestructuringFees %>







            3. Revised Repayment Schedule:






Your repayment will now follow a new schedule, which includes


                        <%= data.tenureInMonth %> EMIs


New EMI due dates: <%= data.newDueDate %>


(Please refer to the EMI schedule enclosed with this document.)






            4. Revised Interest Rate:






The applicable interest rate on your restructured loan is stated in your Revised Sanction
                        Letter. This may be

Fixed

or- Floating, linked to a benchmark rate






            5. Penalty and Late Payment:






Late Payment Charges are <%= data.lateFeesPerDayRate %>% P.A. on the overdue EMI amount.

Set the EMI bounce charges to ₹590 (inclusive of GST)





            6. Prepayment Option:






You have the flexibility to prepay the loan amount or make extra payments without incurring
                        prepayment charges.






            7. Collateral and Security:






 This loan remains unsecured after loan restructuring. 






            8. No Waiver of Original Obligations:






The restructuring does not waive your original loan obligations unless explicitly mentioned. All
                        other terms continue to apply.






            9. Credit Bureau Reporting:







                        As per RBI guidelines, your restructured loan will be reported to credit bureaus. This may
                        impact your credit score.







            10. In Case of Default:






If you default under the restructured terms, we reserve the right to take recovery action as per
                        applicable law and agreement terms—without further notice.






            11. Processing Fees & Charges:






A restructuring or documentation fee (if applicable) will be charged as detailed in your revised
                        sanction letter or KFS (Key Fact Statement).






            12. No Cooling-Off Period:






 Please note that restructured loans do not carry a cooling-off period. Once accepted, the terms
                        are binding.






            13. Legal Framework:






 This restructuring agreement is governed by Indian laws. Any legal disputes will be subject to
                        the jurisdiction of courts located in New Delhi.






            14. Severability:






 If any clause in this agreement is held invalid, the rest shall remain fully effective and
                        enforceable.



        15. Customer Consent:






 By accepting this revised terms, you confirm:- You have read and understood these terms- You
                        accept them voluntarily and without coercion.









